metadata.name: Just, Steven! #425
metadata.description:
Just,Steven - is a shell that has always followed me, or has been a part of me, I never fully understood. This is a character who ironically, because of the many social culture shifts in his life, began to resort to the way of putting other people's faces and stories on himself. At first it was necessary to adapt in a certain circle of society so as not to be a black sheep, after a few years he stopped noticing how the consciousness itself uses the stories or phrases he has already heard from absolutely different people received during a conversation, news or other, another of the features is the numerous personalities of Steven.

I am creating this project because I have long wanted to try to tell people that being yourself is the most difficult and wonderful feeling. My goal is to get an animated movie adaptation on Netflix, the script will be written by anyone who wants to participate in the community. 

Peace be with you all!

metadata.name: Zpritez 3D #1023
metadata.description:
Generates interactive 3D pixel art sprites.
Each character also has a unique sound effect.
There are a variety of styles and backgrounds.
Click or touch to interact, position tweaks the sound.
Right click to save as a 1920x1080 image.

Code is based on my open source sprite generator ZzSprite.
https://github.com/KilledByAPixel/ZzSprite

Audio is using my open source sound effect system ZzFX.
https://github.com/KilledByAPixel/ZzFX

metadata.name: Traces #66
metadata.description:
Traces is an exploration around movement.
Inspired but motion blur in photography, using lines travelling through obstacles, it can create scenes, sometimes representation of virtual landscapes.

Its features include:
- A choice between 12 modern and 7 rarer palette inspired by some of my photographies (revealed on my twitter with the first mint
- 3 definitions
- 3 types of obstacles modifying the motion
- Rare symmetrical dispositions

The art is better viewed in full screen, captures don't display the fine details

Unsold will be burnt after a certain time, and price might increase

metadata.name: Stippled Sketch #143
metadata.description:
Stippled Sketch is an experimental attempt to imitate the result of sitting down and mindlessly finding form on the page. The process of pressing the pen to paper in a rhythmic, repeated pattern can be a form of meditation, much like doodling. 

The form at the center of the sketch can sometimes take a clear and recognizable shape, but it can also appear meandering and meaningless at times. Some forms appear more often than others (such as a clover and circle), but the equation at the core of the algorithm has surprised me quite a few times with unique and unusual shapes, even after reviewing thousands of previews. 

I like to think of this collection as a reflection of a time in my life when I wanted to say so muchâ€”and I could put the pen to the paper, but I knew that no words would have any effect, so I sketched to focus my attention on something else instead.
